Pre-installation
================

RewriteEngine On
RewriteBase /path/to/dirroot
RewriteRule ^dev$ local/dev/index.php
RewriteRule ^dev/(.*)$ local/dev/$1


Installation
============

Prepare a mirror of the vanilla moodle.git repository in the server moodledata.

# mkdir -p moodledata/local_dev/repos
# chown -R apache:apache moodledata/local_dev
# cd moodledata/local_dev/repos
# git clone --mirror git://git.moodle.org/moodle.git
# chown -R apache:apache moodle.git

Run cli/git-commits.php to register commit history (may take a longer time)

Run cli/git-tags.php --import to import prepared tags.txt

Run cli/git-aliases.php --import to import the legacy CVS mappings

Run cli/aggregate.php to generate initial reports for display


Post-installation
=================

Define Git aliases and run cli/aggregate/php to update reports.
